loud.name: Fender 100T Bassman 100 watt amplifier and speaker
loud.description: Fender 100T Bassman 100 watt amplifier with silverface head and blond 410 NED Bassman speaker.  Barely used, purchased in 2013.  Price: $1200 for the head,  $600 for the speaker. Excellent condition. The Fender 100T is powerful and loud, while being very sensitive to the dynamics of the player’s touch. It responds beautifully across the frequency spectrum with a sparkling, harmonically rich tone at low and moderate volumes. At louder volumes it thickens with a sweet distortion that only seems to get creamier the more it’s cranked. It is not just a bass amp but is simply amazing with even my miked acoustic guitar. It has 3 power choices: 100, 25, and 25 watt silent mode. This rarely mentioned feature allows you to record without sound from the speakers but with a recordable full featured sound - after preamp and amp adjustments. Located in Santa Rosa for inspection and pick-up. No shipping/delivery available.

famous.name: Famous FS-1 Soprano Ukulele OBO
famous.description: Pretty little soprano, nice build with super-thin mahogany laminate, but with a sound that will rival most solid-wood ukes. Extremely light, with excellent projection and beautiful resonance. The Famous FS-1 is a Japanese build, identical to the Kiwaya KS-1, but sold only to the Japanese market. This older uke has a Rosewood fingerboard, which you won't find in production any longer...the newer ones are walnut.  Subtle striping at the soundhole is nice touch. Low action and great intonation, it's got a classic ukulele sound. Friction tuners. Tiny scratch on the headstock, mark on the first fret - see the photos for detail.Reasonable offers are welcome.

Original finish but does show slight wear, but very nice for it’s age. No dents & the serial numbers do match, and the original case is in very good condition. Please email with any questions.

famous.name: MXR CSP102SL Script Dyna Comp Reissue
famous.description: Selling a mint-condition MXR CSP102SL Script Dyna Comp Reissue pedal in original box. This was a very recent purchase but I no longer have the need for a compression pedal. Below is the official information on the pedal:The Dyna Comp Compressor is famous for first-rate, no-nonsense approach to tightening up your guitar signal and creating rich, full-bodied sustain. Like the Phase 90, this little red gem is a legend among its kind. The pedals produced in the mid-’70s are particularly prized for their unqiue sound and performance.The Script Dyna Comp Compressor combines that old-school sound with a couple of upgrades for modern gigging convenience. Spec’d from our own 1976 Dyna Comp Compressor, this pedal is built around the rare CA3080 metal can integrated circuit (IC), which yields quieter operation, greater transparency, and increased dynamic range. Thanks to its bypass status LED and AC power jack, you can put this pedal right on your board without worrying over whether the pedal is on or about to lose power.Features    Classic sound with modern upgrades    Quieter operation, greater transparency, and increased dynamic range    Bypass status LED and AC power jackNo trades. Will accept cash, PayPal, or Venmo. Local buyers only. Good luck
